    "DPO is a training paradigm that optimizes the same objective as RLHF, namely PPO, without performing RL, by bypassing the explicit reward estimation and instead using a single maximum likelihood objective.",
    "The DPO's objective is defined as",
    "where π λ and π ref are the policy and reference models respectively, x is the model input and (y w, y l) is the preference pair (with y w being preferred over y l).",
    "Complementary, Ouyang et al. (2022) found that it is beneficial to modify the RLHF training scheme by mixing pretraining gradients into the PPO gradients.",
